</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Sometimes I‚Äôll flirt with playing 6-string versions of the E-Emaj7-E7 sequence, using the voicings shown below. If you do this, try to lead into each chord by playing the bass notes (4th string) as I show here ‚Äî which attempts to capture the very important descending tone. What I don‚Äôt love about this, is how muddy the Emaj7 sounds ‚Äî so if anything, that‚Äôs the chord (of the 3 shown below) where I usually revert to the 4-string version.</p>

