<h2 id="strumming-patterns">Strumming patterns</h2>

<p>The most basic strum you‚Äôll want to do is a ‚Äúbass, DOWN, bass, DOWN‚Äù where ‚Äúbass‚Äù refers to the thickest string used in whatever chord you‚Äôre playing. I slightly emphasize the down-strums.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>[ See PDF for diagram ]
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>To strum like Dylan, use one of the two patterns below. Keep all up-strums light, staying on the thinnest 2-3 strings only. Keeping an accent on beats 2 &amp; 4 also sounds good, if you can manage.</p>

